ar fetching $14.55 million]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132313505.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Jim Irsay's impressive collection of memorabilia fetched more than $105 million at auction, with standout pieces like David Gilmour's guitar commanding a staggering $14.55 million. Items of historical significance, including tickets from Lincoln's assassination, attracted considerable interest. Additionally, the original Alcoholics Anonymous manuscript made its way home for $2.4 million. Profits from the auction will benefit charitable foundations that were dear to the late collector.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/nfl/news/a-late-nfl-owners-collection-sold-for-more-than-105-million-with-one-guitar-fetching-14-55-million/articleshow/132313505.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/nfl/news/a-late-nfl-owners-collection-sold-for-more-than-105-million-with-one-guitar-fetching-14-55-million/articleshow/132313505.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T20:15:29+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132314243,imgsize-107240.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Indian dorctor jailed for 20 years in Tennessee for medical malpractice, attorney says no punishment is enough]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132313971.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Dr Sanjeev Kumar, a gynecologist, was handed a two-decade prison sentence after he was found guilty of tampering with medical devices and perpetrating health fraud. Dr Kumar reused single-use hysteroscopes on multiple female patients, generating fraudulent charges exceeding forty-one million dollars.]]></description><link><![C